n is generated for each message and is encrypted with AES.\r\nThe \"passphrase\" for AES key encryption is \"coded\" in \"Master.txt\" file which is included in the zip file.\r\n\r\nYou can send encrypted channel messages or private messages, only who have the \"Master.txt\" key can view the decrypted message.\r\n\r\nIS VERY IMPORTANT TO CHANGE THE MASTER.TXT KEY\"\r\n\r\nI'm not a programmer, i simply fall in love for this systems, so i've decided to share my little work.\r\n\r\nOh... and i'm sorry for very bad english :)\r\n\r\nVideo and screenshots coming soon....\r\n\r\nP.S.\r\nIn the zip archive the Visual Studio 2010 Solution is called \"i.sln\", i haven't changed it.", "shortname": "crystal-irc", "socialnetworks": [{"accounturl": "", "socialnetwork": "Twitter"}, {"accounturl": null, "socialnetwork": "Facebook"}], "status": "active", "summary": "Encrypt IRC Communications with OTP and AES", "tools": [{"label": "Activity", "mount_point": "activity", "name": "activity"}, {"label": "Files", "mount_point": "files", "name": "files"}, {"label": "Summary", "mount_point": "summary", "name": "summary", "sourceforge_group_id": 2338927}, {"label": "Reviews", "mount_point": "reviews", "name": "reviews"}, {"label": "Support", "mount_point": "support", "name": "support"}, {"label": "Wiki", "mount_point": "wiki", "name": "wiki"}, {"label": "Code", "mount_point": "code", "name": "git"}, {"label": "Tickets", "mount_point": "tickets", "name": "tickets"}, {"label": "Discussion", "mount_point": "discussion", "name": "discussion"}], "url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/crystal-irc/", "video_url": "www.youtube.com/embed/cJcGuf1zID8?rel=0"}
